      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's interesting how you frame it as \"the interests of a few communities\" vs \"the greater good.\" doesn't that make it sound like the people losing everything are just less important? it feels like you've already decided that the environmental outcome is the only thing that matters and the economic reality for these workers is just a side note. isn't that a bit of a biased way to look at a policy decision?",
